name: Wilma Rudolph
occupation: Wilma Rudolph was an American sprinter who, following her successes in the 1956 and 1960 Olympic games,became a world-record-holding champion and an international sports icon in track and field.
achievements: Rudolph became the first American woman to win three gold medals in track and field at a single Olympic game.

name: Simone Biles
occupation: Simone Biles is an American gymnast with 2016 Olympic gold medals in individual all-around, vault, and floor competitions. She was part of the dominant women gymnasts in the 2016 Olympics, dubbed the "Final Five".
achievements: Among Biles' awards are: Best Female Athlete ESPY Award, Laureus World Sports Award for Sportswoman of the Year, BBC Overseas Sports Personality of the Year, Glamour Award for The Record Breaker, Best Female U.S. Olympic Athlete ESPY Award, and the Shorty Award for Best in Sports.

name: Serena Williams
occupation: Serena Williams is an American professsional tennis player who has been ranked by the Women's Tennis Association as No. 1 in the world in singles eight times.
achievements: Serena, and her sister Venus, became the first team to win 3 double golds in the 2012 Olympics. Serena was the oldest player to hold all Grand Slam titles in singles as well as Olympic gold in singles.

name: Missy Franklin
occupation: Melissa, "Missy", Franklin is a professional swimmer and a five-time Olympic gold medalist.
achievements: Missy currently holds the world record in the 200-meter backstroke and the American records in the 100-meter backstroke.

name: Lisa Borders
occupation: Lisa Borders is the current president of the WNBA, and the former Vice President of Global Affairs at Coca-Cola
achievements: In 2010, Lisa became a founding leader of No Labels,  a citizen's movement of Republicans, Democrats and Independents, with the mission of addressing the politics of problem solving.

name: Ibtihaj Muhammed
occupation: Ibtihaj Muhammad is an American sabre fencer as a member of the United States fencing team. She was the first Muslim-American woman to wear a hijab while competing for the United States in the Olympics.
achievements: Ibtihaj earned All-America honors with a record of 49-8. She then went on to place second at the mid-Atlantic/South Regional and 21st at the Junior Olympics. The following year, she finished 11th for saber at the NCAA Championships and earned her second All-America honors, earning her third in 2006.

name: Annie Oakley

name: Val Ackerman
occupation: Valerie Ackerman is the current commissioner of the Big East Conference and is best known for being the first president of the Women's National Basketball Association, serving from 1996-2005.
achievements: She has won many awards including the New Jersey Sportswriters Association Executive of the Year Award in 1998, the March of Dimes Sports Achievement Award in 1997,induction into the GTE Academic All-America Hall of Fame in 1999,the National Mother's Day Committee's, etc. Outstanding Mother Award in 2002.

name: Abby Wambach
occupation: Mary Abigail Wambach is an American retired soccer player and coach.
achievements: Abby is a two-time Olympic gold medalist and FIFA Women's World Cup champion.
